HEADWORD: Bonnet rouge
<hw>Bon`net" rouge"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>The
red cap adopted by the extremists in the French Revolution, which became
a sign of patriotism at that epoch; hence, a revolutionist; a Red
Republican.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

